  <title>Description</title>
  <titlealts>
    <searchtitle>NHS Business Definition: Neonate - Description</searchtitle>
  </titlealts>
  <body>
  <div>
    <p>
A 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_neonate">Neonate</xref>
 is a 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENT</xref>.        </p>
    <p>
A 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_neonate">Neonate</xref>
 is a baby.        </p>
    <p>
A neonatal period commences on the 
              <xref outputclass="element" keyref="element_person_birth_date__baby_">PERSON BIRTH DATE (BABY)</xref>
 and ends 28 completed days after birth.        </p>
    <p>
Note: When a baby is born prematurely the delivery of care in a neonatal setting may continue beyond 28 days after the 
              <xref outputclass="element" keyref="element_person_birth_date__baby_">PERSON BIRTH DATE (BABY)</xref>.        </p>
  </div>
